The attorney general of the federation and minister of justice, Abubakar Malami (SAN) has expressed interest to contest the Kebbi State governorship post under the platform of the All Progressives Congress (APC). Malami made this known yesterday during the APC stakeholders forum held in Birnin Kebbi. The forum was attended by the chairman, APC Governors’ Forum and Kebbi State Governor Abubakar Atiku Bagudu and other chieftains of the party in the state. Malami said: “Today, I come out openly to announce my intention contest for governorship seat of Kebbi State come 2023 if approved by the people of the state and the APC.” He added that if elected, he would respect the good intentions of the people of Kebbi State, especially the APC members and the electorate. He commended Governor Bagudu and the APC Governors Forum, saying his style and leadership had provided a platform for credible leadership of the APC, Kebbi State and Nigeria as a whole. Governor Abubakar Atiku Bagudu who supported Malami’s position to contest, urged the APC in the state to support his candidature to become the next governor of the state. Bagudu described Malami as a true politician who used his good office as minister to restore the image of Kebbi State and Nigeria in the eyes of the world.